===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|citizen}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|*citezein}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|*citezein}} (spelling altered by confusion between ''ʒ'' ([[w:yogh|yogh]] = ''y'') and ''z'', and also possible contamination from {{term|denizen|lang=en}}), from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|citeien|lang=fro}} (Modern French {{term|citoyen|lang=fr}}), from {{term|cite||settlement (regardless of size), later meaning [[cathedral]] town|lang=fro}} (Modern French {{term|cité|lang=fr}}, English {{term|city|lang=en}}), from {{term|citet|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|civitas||citizenship, community of citizens|lang=la}}, from {{term|civis||townsman, citizen|lang=en}} (English {{term|civil|lang=en}}, {{term|civilian|lang=en}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*key-||to lie, homestead}}. Cognate with Old English {{m|ang|hīwan||pos=plural|members of one's household, servants}}. More at {{l/en|hewe}}.

